-- TABLE-Brazil consumer confidence hits lowest since June 2009
-- By Silvio Cascione
-- Fri Jan 24, 2014 05:48AM EST
-- None



BRASILIA, Jan 24 (Reuters) - A gauge of consumer confidence in Brazil dropped in January to its lowest since June 2009, remaining below its historical average for an 11th straight month as a sluggish economic outlook weighed on consumer sentiment.

The consumer confidence measure is calculated by the Fundação Getúlio Vargas (FGV).Expectations index105.6   108.4  110.6